social_posts.post_text: Caught this Mid packing musical performance, if only i could freeze time right here.

In a series of plot twists worthy of at least a season or two of chaotically endearing Modern Family story lines. We bought a house. Next door to our best friends. In a neighborhood that kids dreams are made of. We close in a few days and the way we ended up here really is quite the story. The last two years have been wild in both the best and the worst ways. It’s been a roller coaster of life changes but God’s made Himself known every step of the way and when i look back over every little thing that led us here i am overwhelmed by His goodness, protection, and guidance over us. The way He weaves every single moment of our lives to unfold in His perfect plan and timing is something that will always leave me in awe. We will be sharing every step of our renovations with you guys through our subscription and doing a Q&A about all the details! Bottom line, we are excited, chaotic, tired, and thankful! So, really just the usual. #thehenhouse #obviouslyimphildunphy #thatsalotofadjectives

Now that we are in a neighborhood with friends on every street, we wanted to find something that would allow Bowen and Mera to have that carefree kid fun but also keep them safe (we are covert helicopter parents lol) So, naturally I did way too much research on kid friendly smart watches the last several months, let me tell you these @myticktalk ones came out on top every time. I reached out intending to buy Bowen one and because they are the sweetest company they offered to send us a watch for not just B but Mera too! They have several safety features, gps tracking, school mode, approved only phone calls/text and FaceTime. It’s only $10 a month (pay as you go so no contract) and makes you low key feel like Judy Jetson. They also gave us a code for friends/family/followers (MASA) for $15 off! I swear I’ve shouted this product from every mountain top lately, I’m so excited to see their faces Christmas morning!! #ticktalk4

READ THIS POST. Watching the ones you love most in this world decline is one of the hardest parts of life. Nana is in the ICU they are still trying to determine what’s going on. I had to come back home Sunday and learned yesterday that I brought both the flu and strep home with me. I’m currently quarantined and worn down. This shell of a person is not who I’m used to being, it’s not who i want to be, but it’s who i am right now. I know i will rally, i will trust Jesus, lean on my loved ones and come back to my usual self stronger soon. Until then, If you are waiting on a reply, photos, dms, emails, posts, projects etc please be patient with me. I’m working while sick and emotionally broken. If you’ve worked with me you know i try to go above and beyond for every client, friend, person in my life. I push myself to accommodate others, i put others first bc I truly LOVE being there for those who need me. Im not one to ask for things, and maybe it’s the cough med/vast lack of sleep or ptsd from the down right horrible last year and half talking here, but if I’m being honest I’m finally broken down enough to ask for help and grace while i navigate this time. Your photos are coming, your text and emails will be answered just not all today. I hope and pray you can forgive me and extend some grace my way. I love my people. Thanks for being my people.

It had been almost a year since we lost pawpaw (a milestone we were all dreading) when Bowen brought home the book his class wrote and published together. This was the first time we were able to read what he’d written. While I didn’t have sitting in the driveway, sobbing over a children’s book on my bingo card for that day, somehow that’s where i found myself. 

As parents we want to protect our kids from the heartbreak and pain of losing someone they love, but we know it’s an unavoidable part of life. So, we do what we can to support, love, and pray them through it. Standing there holding the book wishing for a Lazarus moment (or at least the number to @dudeperfect ‘s manager) i knew there was at least one of these three wishes we could actually grant. Turns out it was just the one we needed and that God already had everything in motion. Bowen’s wanted his very own dog (a golden retriever) for a long time, even saving his own money up over the last year. We were already discussing surprising him at Christmas with one until we read this and 2 days later saw a friend share a Facebook post for golden retriever puppies available the very week of pawpaws passing anniversary. The more we looked into it all, the more we saw how God had woven this all together for us. Louie was one of a single litter of 15 puppies to two beautiful/sweet service dogs of a retired veteran. Full blooded, responsibly bred, well taken care of, healthy, with an excellent temperament (not to mention the very specific timing) it was like someone hand picked him out for us. We like to think someone did. 

I am always humbled by the way God weaves joy into our sadness, how He knows exactly what we need even before we do. How he gets specific and creative in the way he meets those needs only deepens my faith that much more. Bringing Louie home one year almost to the exact day we said goodbye to pawpaw allowed us to rewrite the narrative of one of the saddest memories to one with a little joy added. Just the way he would have wanted. #kinglouiethesecond #goldenretriever

So far, so good…. Merry Christmas morning 9 years running! The most joy filled Christmas yet. For so many reasons, including the hilarious moments of recreating our favorite Christmas tradition. #merrychristmasmorning

Do you ever have moments where God shows up in the details so specifically that you feel like as Mera says “OK, Somebody pinch me I have GOT to be dreamin’!”…
Christmas Eve this year we had more than one of those moments. I’m honestly still wrapping my mind around all of the ways God made this day so incredibly special for us and Bowen. Long but stick with me!
Bo decided to have his baptism on Christmas Eve by our good family friend @daviddees14 which was special to begin with. One thing about Bowen is he loves having his people all together. As soon as he chose this day he shared that he really wanted Nana to be there. Knowing how difficult traveling is for her right now he understood the unlikelihood of making this possible. Jump to the day before his baptism I’m in the back and hear him shout “NANA! IT’S NANA!” There were hugs, tears, her and aunt Susan pulled off the best surprise for all of us. Mera said more than once “it’s a Christmas miracle!” Later Nana told us just how much of a miracle it was (see her text above) Bowen felt God’s love so deeply that morning, having nana and even some of his best buddies surprise him by coming to watch him publicly declare his life for Jesus. That alone was enough to fill our cup to overflowing, but God had one more special moment planned. When Bowen was little he learned about four leaf clovers & that finding one is rare/special. Ever since then He’s been on a mission, saying that one day he knew he would find one. He always stops to look here and there anytime we come across a patch, always coming up empty handed. Until, this day. The day of his baptism, walking in our own front yard after service, he reaches down and finds a tiny perfectly intact four leaf clover. Im not sure how in all the excitement he thought to look down, or how in a yard he’s looked in countless times before, he finds one on the very day of his baptism. Except that Jesus knew just what would make him feel the depth of God’s love for him and the small details of our lives. We framed it beside his baptism certificate so we never forget. Buried with Christ in baptism, raised to walk in new life. Christmas Eve Morning 2023 Bowen walks in new life.
